Textbooks were in one of the classrooms that was burnt. JOHANNESBURG - Tokelo Secondary School in Evaton might have to delay the first day of school after a fire on Thursday morning. The blaze caused major damage. Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says thugs are responsible. Textbooks were in one of the classrooms that was burnt. In a tweet, the MEC says there's no money to repair the infrastructure damage caused by the fire. The total loss is estimated to be more than R4-million. Police are investigating possible arson.